          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the sponge",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional. Grease two 20 cm sandwich tins and line the bases. Beat the butter and sugar together until pale and fluffy; this takes 5 minutes with a hand mixer. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Fold in the flour and baking powder, then the coffee extract and chopped walnuts. Divide evenly between the tins and smooth the surfaces. Bake for 22 to 25 minutes until the sponge springs back to a light press and a skewer comes out clean. Leave in the tins for 5 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the buttercream and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the butter until very soft. Add the icing sugar in two batches and beat until pale and smooth, about 3 minutes. Beat in the coffee extract. If the buttercream is stiff, add milk a teaspoon at a time to bring it to a spreading consistency. Place one cooled sponge on a plate and spread with half the buttercream. Place the second sponge on top and spread the remainder over the top; leave the sides plain for the classic version. Press walnut halves around the edge or arrange them in a ring on top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
